Format: https://www.debian.org/doc/packaging-manuals/copyright-format/1.0/
Upstream-Name: yojimbo
Upstream-Contact: Glenn Fiedler <glenn@mas-bandwidth.com>
Source: https://github.com/mas-bandwidth/yojimbo
Files-Excluded: netcode reliable serialize sodium
Comment: The upstream netcode/, reliable/, serialize/ and sodium/ directories
 (vendored copies of their own upstream projects, present so source builds
 have zero dependencies) are stripped from the repacked +ds orig tarball:
 the Debian package is built with -DYOJIMBO_SYSTEM_DEPS=ON against
 libnetcode-dev, libreliable-dev, libserialize-dev and libsodium-dev.
 tlsf/ is retained and compiled into the library — it is a small private
 implementation detail of yojimbo's per-client allocators, has no public
 interface here, and is not separately packaged in Debian.

